@Node "Preface" "Cybertracker.guide/Preface"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Preface@{uu}@{ub}

  Cybertracker is offered to you under the concepts of ShareWare. You
  can use it for an evaluation period of up to 30 days without paying
  any charge. If you are going to use Cybertracker after the evaluation
  period, or to make music you should register, because the save song
  option are disabled in the unregistred version.

  See License and the `README' file for more information.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Introduction" "Cybertracker.guide/Introduction"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

  This manual is a description of Cybertracker, a new tracker for the
  Amiga range of computers.

  Cybertracker requires Kickstart 2.04 or higher to run. It uses many 2.04+
  features and has been designed to be as user-friendly as possible.

  I'm developing this tracker mainly because the lack of good trackers for
  the Amiga. 

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Features" "Cybertracker.guide/Features"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Features@{uu}@{ub}

 * Nice OS2.0 layout

 * Runs on a real intuition-screen.

 * 255 voices

 * 255 channels

 * 65535 patterns

 * 65535 positions

 * Two command channels

 * 255 commands

 * @{" ISS " Link iss} (Independent Sound Systems)

 * @{" External Tools " Link xtools}

 * @{" Fpl Scripts " Link Fpl_scripts}

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Installation" "Cybertracker.guide/Installation"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

  Just place the Cybertracker (CT) drawer anywere on your harddisk.
  No assigns has to been made.


  Notice that Cybertracker requires reqtools.library by Nico François.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Updating" "Cybertracker.guide/Updating"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Updating@{uu}@{ub}

  The same as @{" Installation " Link Installation}, but if you are an registred user, make sure
  that you don't lose your keyfile.

@EndNode

