@Node "Project_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Project menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Project menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Iconify "Amiga I"@{ub}

   Iconfies program and leaves a nice little icon on wb screen.

 @{b}Configuration@{ub}

  @{b}Enviroment@{ub}

     Here you can define on which buttons the @{" External Tools " Link xtools} and @{" Fpl Scripts " Link Fpl_scripts}
     will be executed from.

  @{b}Screenmode@{ub}

     Changes the screenmode of the tracker.

  @{b}Palette@{ub}

     Allows you to define your own set of colours to be present on screen.

  @{b}Save@{ub}

     Saves configuration.

  @{b}Load@{ub}

     Loads a pre stored configuration.

 @{b}About@{ub}

   Shows some author and tracker information.

 @{b}Quit "Amiga Q"@{ub}

   Exits program. If you have changed you song and havn't saved it a
   requester will pop up asking if you would like to.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Song_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Song menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Song menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}New@{ub}

  Will clear all patterns and voices in the voicelist. A requseter will
  pop up and ask you how many channels the new song will be produced in. 

 @{b}Load "Amiga L"@{ub}

  Loads a pre stored song in cybertracker format.

 @{b}Save "Amiga S"@{ub}

  Saves present song in cybertracker format.

 @{b}Edit Data "Amiga E"@{ub}

  Allows you to type in the songs author info and edit the @{" ISS " Link iss} patch bay.

 @{b}Play "Amiga P"@{ub}

  Plays song.

 @{b}Stop "Amiga O"@{ub}

  Stops song.

 @{b}Record to@{ub}

  This function will copy the audio output to a IFF sample file. This function
  is not implemented yet mainly because it's a bit complex to do. 

 @{b}Generate Replay Source@{ub}

  Generates a optimized replysource for the current song. The optimaztion is
  based on the current song and therefore the replaysource can't be used together
  with another song. Not implemented yet, Sorry.

 @{b}Transpose@{ub}

  Transposes the whole song. For more info see @{" Transpose Window " Link Transpose_Window}

 @{b}Change number of channels@{ub}

  Let you change the number of channels in the present song. Notice that if you
  choose a decrese of the amount of channels the highest ones will be stripped and
  lost into cyberspace.

 @{b}Remove@{ub}

	 @{b}/unused patterns@{ub}

	Removes all unused patterns.

	 @{b}/unused voices@{ub}

	Removes all unused voices.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Pattern_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Pattern menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Pattern menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}New "Amiga N"@{ub}

  Creates a new pattern.

 @{b}Load@{ub}

  Loads a pre stored pattern from disk. (not functional)

 @{b}Save@{ub}

  Saves marked pattern to disk. (not functional)

 @{b}Edit Data@{ub}

  Currently, there is no data to edit.

 @{b}Delete "Amgia D"@{ub}

  Allows you to chose a pattern to delete from the pattern list.

 @{b}Change Size@{ub}

  Allows you to change size of a marked pattern. You may chose steps in
  range of 1 to 64 steps.

 @{b}Cut "Alt F3"@{ub}

  Clears all information in the pattern, and strips it to the
  copy buffer.

 @{b}Copy "Alt F4"@{ub}

  Copies all information in the pattern.

 @{b}Paste "Alt F5"@{ub}

  Overwrites a hole pattern with the information currently in the
  pattern copy buffer.

 @{b}Transpose@{ub}

  Transpose current pattern. For more info see @{" Transpose Window " Link Transpose_Window}

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Track_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Track menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Track menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Load@{ub}

  Loads a pre stored track to the track you are standing in.

 @{b}Save@{ub}

  Saves the track you are standing in to disk.

 @{b}Cut "Shift F3"@{ub}

  Erases currntly active track from tracker to copy buffer.

 @{b}Copy "Shift F4"@{ub}

  Copies trackinformation to copy buffer.

 @{b}Paste "Shift F5"@{ub}

  Will paste all information in the copy buffer to the currently
  active track.

 @{b}Transpose@{ub}

  Transpose current track. For more info see @{" Transpose Window " Link Transpose_Window}
  
@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Block_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Block menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Block menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Mark "Amiga B"@{ub}

  Will mark a defined area of the track.

 @{b}Paste "Amiga V"@{ub}

  Will paste all information in the copy buffer to your position
  in the track.

 @{b}Copy "Amiga C"@{ub}

  Downloads marked information to copy buffer.

 @{b}Cut "Amiga X"@{ub}

  Erases currently marked area.

 @{b}Clear "Amiga Z"@{ub}

  Simply clears the block without copying it to the clipboard.

 @{b}Transpose@{ub}

  Transpose marked block. For more info see @{" Transpose Window " Link Transpose_Window}

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Voices_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Voices menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Voices menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Load "Amiga 1"@{ub}

  Attemp to load a sample to the currently marked sample position.

 @{b}Save "Amiga 2"@{ub}

  Will save the marked sample to the name it says in the voice list.
  
 @{b}Kill "Amiga 3"@{ub}

  Will remove currently marked sample from both memory and the
  voice list.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Import_menu" "Cybertracker.guide/Import menu"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Import menu@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Protracker Module "Amiga K"@{ub}

  Loads a protracker module.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "Transpose_Window" "Cybertracker.guide/Transpose Window"
@Toc "Menus"


 @{u}@{b}Transpose window@{uu}@{ub}


  Transposing lets you shift the pitch of the notes up or down, on one
  or all samples -36 to +36 steps in your song. E.g change a C-3 to C#3.

  In the Transpose window you can use the follwing keyboard keys:

	@{b}+@{ub}       Increase the pitch shift

	@{b}-@{ub}       Decrease the pitch shift

	@{b}[Space]@{ub} Toggle transpose mode

	@{b}O@{ub}       Do it!

	@{b}C@{ub}       Cancel

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************
* TRACKER Features **********************************************************
*****************************************************************************

@Node "Tracker_Features" "Cybertracker.guide/Tracker Features"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Tracker Features@{uu}@{ub}


 @{"  Keyboard Shortcuts  " Link Keyboard_Shortcuts}


 Definition: Track and Channel is the same thing.

 Please note the difference between position and patternposition.

 Any piece of music written with Cybertracker is built up from patterns.
 The patterns is combined to a song with positions. It shouldn't be to
 hard to understand.

 Each pattern is built up from x-number of tracks, depending on how many
 logic channels there are present in the song.

 To be able to change anything the Tracker must be in editmode, this is
 indicated by the cursor when it's filled. Toggle editmode on/off with [SPACE]

 A pattern is built up like this:

          A Track
      ________________
     |                |
     |          ++---++-EffectArgument
     |          ||   ||
     |          ||   ||
   00  C-3 01 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   01  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   02  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   03  C#3 01 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   04  D-3 01 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   05  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   06  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
   /    /  |/ \|   |/
  /    /   |    \  |
Pos Note Voice Effect cmd.
     (1)  (2)     (3)


 1. The note describes at which frequency the voice will be played. 

 2. The voice column describes which of the voices to be played.

 3. Then you have two effect channels. Here you can write commands as
    arguments to the note or commands which affect the songs movement. 
    As you can see every command is splitted up as xxyy Where xx is the
    command and yy is the argument. All commands over EF (eg F0+) is
    treated as @{" song control commands " link sccoms}.


  When the song is played the patterndata is continuously moved forward.
  When it reaches the end of a pattern, the tracker scrolls the positionlist
  one step forward and activates with the position and it's connected pattern.
  For each step forward in the patterndata, the tracker sends for each track
  the notes with it's voice number and arguments to corresponding @{" ISS Channel" Link iss}.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************

@Node "sccoms" "Cybertracker.guide/Song Control Commands"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}Song Control commands@{uu}@{ub}

  @{u}@{b}F0xx - Set song speed@{uu}@{ub}

	Sets the number of ticks between each patternrow. This
	can be altered to change the speed of the song,	lower
	value is faster. Keep in mind that because all the
	commands except some of them is invoked every tick
	and changing this may seriously change the way the
	commands work. If you must change the speed of the song
	it's better to use F1 (see below).


	Note: F000 stops song.


  @{u}@{b}F1xx - Set song bpm@{uu}@{ub}

	The bpm control the general speed of the song
	and the commands. Default to $7D (125). 
	
  @{u}@{b}FCxx - Note Delay@{uu}@{ub}

	Delays note xx number of ticks.

  @{u}@{b}FDxx - Pattern Break@{uu}@{ub}

	Jumps to next position and starts at patternposition xx (decimal)

  @{u}@{b}FExx - Pattern Delay@{uu}@{ub}

	Delays xx number of ticks.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************
* KEYBORAD ******************************************************************
*****************************************************************************

@Node "Keyboard_Shortcuts" "Cybertracker.guide/Keyboard Shortcuts"
@Toc "Tracker_Features"


 @{u}@{b}Keyboard Shortcuts@{uu}@{ub}

 High notekeys:  2 3   5 6 7   9 0   =
                Q W E R T Y U I O P [ ]
                   
 Low notekeys:    S D   G H J   L ;
                 Z X C V B N M , . /

 [HELP]		- Displays this doc, if availible in docs drawer.

 [SPACE]	- Toggle editmode on/off

 F1 		- Choose 1st octave (From C-0 to G-2)
 F2 		- Choose 2nd octave (From C-1 to G-3)
 F3 		- Choose 3rd octave (From C-2 to G-4)
 F4 		- Choose 4th octave (From C-3 to G-5)
 F5 		- Choose 5th octave (From C-4 to G-6)

 F6 		- Go to patterncue 1   pos 0
 F7 		- Go to patterncue 2   pos 1/4 of patternlength
 F8 		- Go to patterncue 3   pos 2/4 of patternlength
 F9 		- Go to patterncue 4   pos 3/4 of patternlength
 F10		- Go to patterncue 5   pos 4/4 of patternlength

 Shift+F3 	- Cut track to clipboard.
 Shift+F4 	- Copy track to clipboard.
 Shift+F5 	- Paste track clipboard to track.

 Alt+F3 	- Cut whole pattern to clipboard.
 Alt+F4 	- Copy whole pattern to clipboard.
 Alt+F5 	- Paste pattern clipboard to pattern.

 Alt+A-Z 	- Launch one of the @{" External Tools " Link xtools} or @{" Fpl Scripts " Link Fpl_scripts}
		  configured in the @{" Environment Window " Link envwin}.
 
 Tab		- Next track
 Shift+Tab	- Previous track

 
 Arrow Up	- Scroll up in the patternlist
 Arrow Down	- Scroll down in the patternlist
 Arrow Left	- Move left in patternlist
 Arrow Right	- Move right in patternlist


 Shift+Up	- Previous voice
 Shift+Down	- Next voice

 [Return]	- Play current line.

 Shift+[BS]	- Removes current line in patterndata.
 Shift+[Return]	- Inserts a line in patterndata.

 ~ (Below ESC)	- Toggle current channel on or off.


 @{u}@{b}Numeric Shortcuts@{uu}@{ub}

 [		- Previous track.
 ]		- Next track.
 * 		- Activates pattern name gadget.
 -		- Remove a position.
 +		- Add a position.
 [Enter]	- Start song.
 .		- Continue song.
 0 		- Stop song.
 7		- Previous pattern.
 1		- Next pattern.
 8		- Previous position.
 5		- First position or last if at first. (huh ?)
 2		- Next position.

@EndNode

*****************************************************************************
* X-TOOLS *******************************************************************
*****************************************************************************

@Node "xtools" "Cybertracker.guide/External Tools"
@Toc "Main"


 @{u}@{b}External Tools@{uu}@{ub}

   These are standard Amiga Executables which also is executed as standrad
   executables. This means that you can run a tool from a shell whenever the
   tracker is running. But the best way to run these tools is to add them to
   the list in the @{" Environment Window " Link envwin}. Then they are simply
   activated with the Alt+ A-Z keycombination in the tracker.

   The following tools is currently present in the Cybertracker 
   distribution archive:

   @{" Sample Editor " Link "/tools/sampleed/sampleed.guide/main" 0} - An editor for the IFF 8SVX Samples
   @{" FourierLab    " Link "/tools/fourierlab/fourierlab.guide/main" 0} - An advanced FFT editor for the IFF 8SVX Samples


 @{u}@{b}Some notes about external tools@{uu}@{ub}

 * It's possible to have more than one tool running simultaneously, even several
   copies of the same tool.

 * The * (Asterix) on the numeric keyboard will then wrap around round all
   the tools and the tracker itself - Just like Amiga-M does, but only through
   the tools.

 * If a new song is loaded all tools will automagicly be closed, this
   is due to all the troubbles with crosspointing.

 * All tools can be exited with the esc key.

@EndNode

